From a7b0f57957b61d3f9ebd420f4dd316611eb6391e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: John Jakeman <jdjakem@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 6 Dec 2025 18:41:22 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 02/18] Refactor time integrators with adjoint support for
 gradient computation

Add complete adjoint method implementation for time-dependent problems:

Time Steppers:
- Forward Euler (1st order explicit) with full adjoint support
- Backward Euler (1st order implicit) with full adjoint support
- Heun/RK2 (2nd order explicit) with full adjoint support
- Crank-Nicolson (2nd order implicit) with full adjoint support

Each stepper implements:
- param_jacobian for dR/dp
- adjoint_diag_jacobian and adjoint_off_diag_jacobian for adjoint solve
- adjoint_initial_condition and adjoint_final_solution for boundary handling
- quadrature_samples_weights for consistent time integration

Functionals:
- EndpointFunctional: Q = y_k(T) at final time
- TransientMSEFunctional: MSE over observations with optional noise parameter

Infrastructure:
- Unified protocols in protocols.py
- TimeIntegrator with solve(), solve_adjoint(), gradient() methods
- LinearODEResidual benchmark for testing

Tests:
- test_adjoint_jacobian.py verifies gradient via finite differences
- All 4 stepper types pass adjoint Jacobian verification
