From e61801ada91228108a244ee0d480003f65c2bd8b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: John Jakeman <jdjakem@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 6 Dec 2025 19:28:28 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 04/18] Fix HVP sign conventions and add explicit scheme
 handling for time integrators
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Fix second adjoint RHS sign convention based on Heinkenschloss Algorithm 4.1
  - Our forward sensitivity w = dy/dp·v = -w_Heinkenschloss
  - Second adjoint RHS: -∇_{yy}L·w - ∇_{yu}L·v (instead of +∇_{yy}L·w)
  - HVP accumulation: +∇_{uy}L·w (instead of -∇_{uy}L·w)

- Add explicit scheme handling for Forward Euler and Heun
  - For explicit schemes, residual depends on y_{n-1}, so HVP uses w_{n-1}
  - Add _is_explicit_scheme() helper method

- Update HVP tests to use DerivativeChecker with error_ratio tolerance 1e-6
  - Add TimeAdjointOperatorWrapper for DerivativeChecker compatibility
  - Use fewer time steps (3 instead of 10) to avoid accumulated numerical errors

- Add sympy_hvp_derivation.py for symbolic verification of HVP formulas

Backward Euler HVP tests now pass for both quadratic ODE and quadratic ODE + MSE
functional cases. Forward Euler, Crank-Nicolson, and Heun still need debugging.
