From 2df3855f736eb6c1d196cbc43693505f4b1c68e1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: John Jakeman <jdjakem@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 7 Dec 2025 13:11:41 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 11/18] Vectorize Jacobian operations removing Python loops

Replace Python loops with vectorized operations for C++ portability:
- DenseJacobian.__add__/__sub__ with DiagJacobian: use arange and modulo
  for index computation instead of nested loops
- DiagJacobian.get_jacobian(): vectorized scatter using index arrays
- DiagJacobian.rdot(): 3D broadcasting instead of loop over input functions
---
 .../collocation/operators/jacobian_types.py   | 94 ++++++++++++-------
 1 file changed, 59 insertions(+), 35 deletions(-)

