From db00257ff8d84b2f4126d02032f7ae17df3dda6c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: John Jakeman <jdjakem@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 7 Dec 2025 14:23:06 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 18/18] Add Phase 7: ADR physics with parameterized diffusion

Implements PDE physics infrastructure for spectral collocation:

Base classes:
- AbstractPhysics with boundary condition support
- AbstractScalarPhysics, AbstractVectorPhysics

AdvectionDiffusionReaction physics:
- Diffusion: D * laplacian(u) or div(D * grad(u)) for variable D
- Advection: -v . grad(u)
- Reaction: r * u
- Forcing: f(t)
- Analytical Jacobian (df/du)

AdvectionDiffusionReactionWithParam:
- Parameterized diffusion: D = D_base + sum_i param_i * phi_i
- Parameter Jacobian (df/dp) for adjoint sensitivity analysis
- Initial condition parameter Jacobian

Features:
- Factory functions: create_steady_diffusion, create_advection_diffusion
- Tests with manufactured solutions and finite difference verification
- 13 new tests, 149 total tests passing in collocation module
